{"build_type":"library","description":"Bare-metal multi-service supervisor: NO Linux processes. Its whole body is one as-completed launch -- the assessor feed-supervisor-services-into-collector reads the declared services and feeds each into the collector, and the per-item worker load-and-invoke-service-passing-request loads+runs each service binary through the runtime name-to-address linker as its own clone-thread worker. Perpetual services keep the collector parked; restart-on-death is temporarily disabled. No fork, no execve, no signals -- everything is launch.","module_name":"supervise-multiple-managed-services-declared-together","package_name":"supervise-multiple-managed-services-declared-together","function_definitions":{"supervise-multiple-managed-services-declared-together":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"context","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"launch_worker_binary","target_binary":"load-and-invoke-service-passing-request","assessor_binary":"feed-supervisor-services-into-collector","cycle_type":"as-completed"}]}}}